<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1451,1846,2089]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,284,1846,1872]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Description:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis box="[312,461,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Spermogonia</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[517,578,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">aecia</emphasis>
not found. 
<emphasis box="[709,809,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Uredinia</emphasis>
rarely found. 
<emphasis box="[970,1142,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Urediniospores</emphasis>
20.5–25.0 × 17.5–21.5 µm (av. 23.0 × 19.5 µm); walls, 1.4–2.2 µm (av. 1.7 µm). 
<emphasis box="[779,834,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Telia</emphasis>
amphigenous, compact, black, erumpent. 
<emphasis box="[1324,1451,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Teliospores</emphasis>
broadly clavate, ellipsoid, mostly conical or rounded at apices, constricted at the septa, attenuate at the bases, 41.0– 55.5 × 15.0–20.0 µm (49.5 × 17.5 µm); walls brown, 0.6–1.3 µm (av. 0.9 µm) thick at sides, 6.0–10.7 µm (av. 8.3 µm) at apices; pedicels persistent, hyaline, 20.5–49.5 µm (av. 30.5 µm) long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
